    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is an investment-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD) in showroom condition. This example features the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, producing smooth, linear boost across the powerband. The drivetrain is centered around a precise five-speed manual gearbox and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal torque distribution. Mechanically, the car is beyond reproach; recent compression testing shows high, uniform pulses across all rotor faces. The cooling system has been upgraded with a dual-pass aluminum radiator to manage thermal loads, and the intricate vacuum system has been fully refreshed with high-grade silicone lines. The chassis retains its original double-wishbone suspension geometry, offering the surgical handling characteristics these cars are famed for. The exterior finish is flawless with no evidence of clear coat failure, while the notoriously delicate interior plastics remain supple and crack-free. This is a rare, turnkey opportunity for a collector to acquire a mechanically synchronized JDM icon.",
      "price": 44800.0,
